headlines.description: — Payton Pritchard scored a career-high 38 points and the NBA-best Boston Celtics rested their entire starting lineup in a 132-122 victory over the Washington Wizards on Sunday in the teams’ regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Payton Pritchard scores career-high 38 points in Celtics' 132-122 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Nick Smith Jr. scored a season-high 24 points and Steve Clifford won his coaching farewell as the Charlotte Hornets rallied to beat the playoff-bound...
headlines.shortLinkText: Steve Clifford wins final game as Charlotte coach, Hornets beat playoff-bound Cavaliers 120-110

headlines.description: — Myles Turner had 31 points and Pascal Siakam scored 28 as the Indiana Pacers beat the Atlanta Hawks 157-115 on Sunday and avoided falling into the play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Myles Turner scores 31, Pacers avoid play-in tournament with 157-115 rout of Hawks

headlines.description: — After a 46-win regular season, the Miami Heat still aren't in the playoffs. It'll take one more victory to get that job done.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat tune up for postseason by topping Raptors 118-103 in regular-season finale

events.name: Chicago Bulls at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson didn't know where things stood around the NBA as the Knicks were deep into their final game of the regular season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson carries Knicks into No. 2 seed in Eastern Conference, scores 40 points in OT win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 26 points, Franz Wagner added 25 and Jonathan Isaac headed a shutdown defensive effort in his second start of the season for the Orlando Magic, who secured the No. 5 spot in the Eastern Conference on Sunday with a 113-88 win...
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Bucks 113-88 to finish fifth in East, will play Cavaliers in first round of playoffs

headlines.description: — After eight straight wins to end the regular season, the 76ers are set for their first play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid sits out as 76ers zip past Nets 107-86. Philly will face Miami in the play-in tournament

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 21 points, Nikola Jokic had 15 points and 15 rebounds, and the defending champion Denver Nuggets secured the No. 2 seed in the Western Conference with a 126-111 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Defending champion Nuggets finish second in West, beating Grizzlies 126-111

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 36 points on 6-for-6 shooting from 3-point range and the Phoenix Suns beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 125-106 on Sunday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns skip play-in by toppling T-wolves 125-106 to set up 1st-round rematch

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — LeBron James closed out his 21st NBA regular season looking invigorated, formidable on both ends of the court and ready to produce in the postseason.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James' triple-double lifts Lakers over Pelicans and into a play-in rematch with New Orleans

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — With about 90 seconds remaining, Oklahoma City's fans stood in unison and began chanting.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder rout Mavericks 135-86 to take the No. 1 seed in the Western Conference

events.name: Detroit Pistons at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Sandro Mamukelashvili had 18 points and the San Antonio Spurs routed the Detroit Pistons 123-95 on Sunday to close disappointing seasons that both franchises hope will lead to promising futures.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Spurs topple injury-depleted Pistons 123-95 to close disappointing seasons

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Steve Kerr firmly believes his team still has a shot to make a splash this postseason — facing a familiar foe to start the uphill quest.
headlines.shortLinkText: Without Curry, Green, the Warriors beat the Jazz 123-116 and wind up with the 10th seed in the West

headlines.description: — Rookie Cam Whitmore scored 21 points and the Houston Rockets beat the playoff-bound Los Angeles Clippers 116-105 on Sunday to finish at .500 season and avoid a fourth straight losing season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets beat playoff-bound Clippers 116-105 to salvage a .500 season. Kawhi Leonard still out for LA

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 24 points and the Sacramento Kings assured themselves of at least one more home game by beating the Portland Trail Blazers 121-82 in the teams' regular-season finale on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: The Kings beat the Blazers 121-82 in regular season finale to earn at least 1 more home game
